tical enquiry in the expanding interdisciplinary field of space studies. It will be of immediate interest to students and researchers working not only in film studies and film philosophy, but also in French/Francophone studies, postcolonial studies, gender and cultural studies.Listen to James S. Williams speaking about his book http://bit.ly/13xCGZN. (Copy and paste the link into your browser)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion pictureszFrance. 0aPerceptionxIn motion pictures. 0aSpace in motion pictures. 0aSubjectivity in motion pictures. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAbdellatif Kechiche.  aBruno Dumont.  aClaire Denis.  aFrench cinema film critic.  aLaurent Cantet.  aMarseilles.  aRobert Guediguian.  acinematographic space.  acultural space.  adiasporic communities.  afiction cinema.  anarrative space.  arealism.  ascreenspace.  asocial integration.  asocial relations.  asoundscape.  aspectatorial space.  avisual arts.1 aWilliams, James S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610221840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526102218423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526102218/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles